<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Composition and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A single species only (
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. folium" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="folium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">V. folium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), endemic to Madagascar (Belanono).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Noun of neuter gender. From Malagasy &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">valala</emphasis>
&quot; or &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">vahalala</emphasis>
&quot;- grasshopper and Latinized Ancient Greek &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">phyllum</emphasis>
&quot; - leaf
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
